sub_title: MSc Crisis and Security Management, Bachelor in Criminology and Public Policies of Prevention
summary:
Hello! I would like to first present myself as a motivated, very communicative, and curious social scientist with a drive to learn continuously and meaningfully contribute to the projects I work for. I want to work with and for people, and I am ready to take on any challenge ahead of me. 

At the moment I have already completed a Bachelor's in Criminology and a Master's in Crisis and Security Management (with a focus on extremism). While all branches of social and behavioral sciences call my attention, I am deeply interested in the analysis of conflict (and risk) phenomena and behavior from an integral standpoint, especially for the purposes of prevention, reintegration, reparation, and resilience. 

On the other hand, my experience as an educator has also sparked my interest in the field of human development, psychology, and social work, and more broadly, in projects that involve human interaction and communication.

I would be glad to hear from anyone who is interested in my profile; I am always open to connecting and discussing new possibilities!
